<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>There is supposed to be a quest to restore you</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack">TheBlack</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:03 p.m. 29/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> There is supposed to be a quest to restore you<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1785" TARGET=_self>PvP...and my mistake!</A> (Ettel)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Brad said there would be a quest to restore you back to normal status. I am not sure it was ever implemented. I suggest you petition a GM in-game and ask. Those here are interested in being PvP al the time, so it's unlikely anyone here knows how to turn that status off even if it can be done.
<P>&gt; ok, in Felwithe, I was talking to some Priest NPC and he was
<BR>&gt; talking about being a "child of order" and me,
<BR>&gt; thinking quickly, thought this was some kind of quest so I
<BR>&gt; handed him my Tome and Discord Book and BAM my PvP is on....big
<BR>&gt; mistake I thought since I never wanted it on...was wondering, is
<BR>&gt; there any possible way to remove your PvP without having to
<BR>&gt; delete and restart your character?
<BR>&gt; Thanks!
<BR>&gt; Ettel
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
